> Mild, earthy, sweet, and perfect for stuffing, poblano peppers are one of our favorite
> ingredients to use for quick (and delicious!) weeknight dinners. Speaking of stuffing,
> we combined saucy pork with black beans and Southwestern spices for a protein-packed twist
> on the traditional Italian profile. Once filled, the peppers receive a sprinkle of melty
> cheddar, a scattering of fresh tomato salsa, and a drizzle of smoky red pepper–lime crema.
> Yep, these packed peps are sure to satisfy.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @poblano pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Dice @roma tomato{1}. Halve,
peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain and rinse
@black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Place poblano halves on a #baking sheet{} and rub all over with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and softened, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, 2 TBSP onion (4 TBSP for 4 servings),
half the lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

In a separate small bowl, combine @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon}, remaining
lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Add
@water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining
onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}; season with salt
and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the beans
(use the rest as you like), and @water{1/4%cup} to pan with pork filling. Stir
until mixture is saucy and thoroughly combined, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season generously with
salt and pepper.

Once poblano halves are done roasting, remove #baking sheet{} from oven. Stuff with up
to half the filling (save the rest for serving). Evenly sprinkle with
@white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}.

Return to oven until cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Divide remaining filling between plates; top with stuffed poblanos, salsa, and crema.
Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on
the side.